a little late getting started.

653
00:35:37,674 --> 00:35:40,319
I remember a guy that
used to live on this street.

654
00:35:40,332 --> 00:35:42,071
He taught my daughter to swim.

655
00:35:42,149 --> 00:35:45,057
He made a killer barbecue tri-tip.

656
00:35:45,058 --> 00:35:47,195
He had a laugh you could
hear three houses away.

657
00:35:47,196 --> 00:35:51,059
- I liked that guy.
- I'm not that man anymore.

658
00:35:53,411 --> 00:35:54,956
I think you can be.

659
00:36:02,703 --> 00:36:04,681
Oh, you know, I'll be right back.

660
00:36:08,305 --> 00:36:10,673
What the hell are you doing?
I asked you not to come here.

661
00:36:10,674 --> 00:36:13,141
I know, but Paul is suffering,

662
00:36:13,142 --> 00:36:15,062
and everyone else
has turned their back on him.

663
00:36:15,063 --> 00:36:17,419
You know why?
'Cause he's a bad guy!

664
00:36:17,633 --> 00:36:19,222
Look, you might
have fallen for his act,

665
00:36:19,223 --> 00:36:22,662
